<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="58">(Map 1). Myanmar: Mandalay (Mogok = Ruby Mines).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="58" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="58">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="58">
This species is only known from its type locality, Ruby Mines (= Mogok), Myanmar at present. Based on our examination of photos of the holotype, the distribution of this species in Yunnan, reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pu, FJ" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing" pageId="33" pageNumber="82" pagination="588 - 623" title="Coleoptera: Disteniidae and Cerambycidae. The Comprehensive Scientific Expedition to the Qinghai-Xizang Plateau." volumeTitle="Insects of the Hengduan Mountains Region" year="1992">Pu (1992)</bibRefCitation>
is considered a misidentification of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pseudoechthistatus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudoechthistatus pufujiae" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pufujiae">Pseudoechthistatus pufujiae</taxonomicName>
sp. n., which is described in this paper.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
